    "id": "f_csv_1729be6a0c",
    "slug": "we-believe-that-information-is-an-enlightening-agent-but-i-can-assure-you-it-is",
    "texto": "We believe that information is an enlightening agent, but I can assure you it is not. We consume information, but we can’t read. We forgot how to sit down and engage the dense layers of a text. We are so busy devouring information that we forgot how to dance with ideas. We confuse linguistic bits of data for knowledge and ideas. I can assure you, gentlemen, they are not the same. Ideas require effort and the kind of sensibility that engages the subtle layers of meaning. What the hell does information require?",
